The paper deals with visual recognition tasks and unsupervised learning of convolutional neural networks, which are primarily studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also discusses the design of a network architecture, which involves feature extraction and parameter reduction, indicating relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on image classification benchmarks, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques such as text classification.
